findingsText:
 Dr Alessandro La Torre (postdoctoral researcher employed on this project) is responsible for preparation of carbon nanomaterials with well-determined structure and properties. In the past 6 months he carried out the following tasks:
1) Production of MWNT in either long (as manufactured) or short forms;
2) Labeling of these MWNT with Ag NPs;
3) Characterisation of these different forms of MWNT in three types of seawater – filtered, unfiltered and unfiltered with mussel exudate (provided by PU) – using UV-vis spectroscopy, TEM and DLS. Well-characterised carbon nanostructures with their behaviour studied in seawater are essential for the next stage of this collaborative project where there interactions with living organisms in marine environment will be studied in the University of Plymouth.
Carbon nanostructures labelled in Nottingham with rare metal markers will be essential to trace the fate of these materials in living organisms and for electron microscopy studies in the next phase of the project. Agriculture, Food and Drink,Environment
